PROBLEM DECOMPOSITION


Log-in/Sign-up page - Gives the user the choice to log in, if they have an existing account within the application, or sign up to create a new account within the application. Users will be asked to input their username and password.

Basic Information page - After signing up, the user must enter basic information, such as their surname and grade level, as the cafeteria bases its transactions on surname and grade level. Additionally, they will also be asked what their method of transaction will be, either cash, by card, or Gcash (or any online payment method available), or all of them. They may also change their basic information anytime, given they enter their password first within the application.

Order Information page - Once logging in, the user will be able to choose from two categories: snacks and meals. ‘Snacks’ are defined as branded items like ‘Chips Ahoy’ and ‘Oreos’, with drinks sold separately. They will also include the snacks Pisay Co-op sells, e.g nachos and burgers. Obviously, the school materials the Pisay Coop sells are excluded. In the ‘Meals’ section, rice meals, and, unlike ‘Snacks’, will have an option to be sold with an available drink accompanying the meal as an optional add-on. 

Final Price page - Since the user has already completed listing their payment method, once they finish filling out their order, they will be met with a page that has added all the prices of the items they ordered, with the previously selected payment method written underneath. Once it is breaktime or lunch, the user may walk to the canteen or Coop to pick up their order, this also acts like a receipt.
